igen auf, wie Menschen und Dinge in unterschiedlichen historischen und gegenwärtigen Settings von Pflege und Care interagieren und wie Objekte dazu beitragen können, Normalität, Nähe oder Wissen herzustellen bzw. zu verhindern.Mit Fotografien von Thomas Bruns.  aWhether it be disposable gloves or high-tech devices - objects play a huge role in nursing and care. But how do they contribute to the constitution of nursing and care? How are societal ideas and orders inscribed in objects of care and what influence do objects have on their development? This book brings back into focus questions heretofore neglected in relevant research and shows how people and objects interact in historic and contemporary settings of nursing and care, as well as how objects can both contribute to and hinder normality, proximity, or knowledge.  afunded by BMBF  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Nov 2021) 0aAlter. 0aCulture. 0aKulturwissenschaft. 0aMedizin. 4aAlter. 4aCare. 4aCultural Studies. 4aDinge. 4aKultur. 4aKulturanthropologie. 4aKulturwissenschaft. 4aMaterial Culture Studies. 4aMedizin. 4aMensch-Ding-Interaktion. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Gerontology.2bisacsh  aAging Studies.  aCultural Anthropology.  aCultural Studies.  aCulture.  aMaterial Culture Studies.  aMedicine.  aThings.1 aArtner, Lucia, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aArtner, Lucia, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aAtzl, Isabel, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aAtzl, Isabel, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aBruns, Thomas.1 aBöhringer, Daniela, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDepner, Anamaria, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDepner, Anamaria, eeditor.4